   341	### Reading Journey Contract
   342	
   343	The reading-journey reference should tell the orchestrator to extract and record:
   344	
   345	- story order and dependency notes
   346	- story ids using the canonical filename-derived convention
   347	- whether the tech design is a 2-doc or 4-doc pack
   348	- the presence of prompt insert files
   349	- project verification commands
   350	- any current blockers or ambiguous prerequisites
   351	
   352	It should not ask the orchestrator to load provider-specific invocation details at this stage. Those belong in the CLI operations and prompt-system references and are only needed once initialization has succeeded.
   353	
